{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/wrapper","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For macOS applications that require a C\/C++ interface, it may be possible to use NixUniversalSDK indirectly. For example, the SDK download provides a project ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"example-macos-wrapper"},{"type":"text","text":" which allows for its usage in C\/C++ applications."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This project contains single ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/IDeviceScanner","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/IDeviceCompat"},{"text":" instances. It provides a static interface to access these instances and also provides callbacks for device and scanner events. The project contains a basic implementation, but can be modified or expanded to better suit your specific application.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wrapper project is part of the SDK examples which are available "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.nixsensor.com\/sdk-ios","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Building-the-wrapper-project","text":"Building the wrapper project","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is recommended to build the wrapper from the terminal using the provided build script. This script depends on the ‘Command Line Tools for Xcode’, which are available from the Apple Developer ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/download\/all\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","tex